TITLE: Bipartisan immigration framework includes 14% Border Patrol pay hike, visa recapture
SUMMARY: The immigration framework being discussed as a potential last-minute deal in the lame duck session would hike Border Patrol pay by 14% and recapture employment visas.

TITLE: Ex-Twitter counsel James Baker's wife registered voters for Hillary Clinton in 2016, posts reveal
SUMMARY: The wife of James Baker, the Twitter lawyer fired by Elon Musk for his role in suppressing the Hunter Biden laptop story, registered voters for Hillary Clinton in 2016.

TITLE: Hunter Biden seen at ritzy NYC art gallery selling his paintings for up to $200k, despite ethics concerns
SUMMARY: First Son Hunter Biden was spotted Friday at his ritzy SoHo art gallery exhibition with his family as a congressional ethics probe into his international business dealings looms.

TITLE: Biden administration funds study on how to train drug addicts to distribute COVID tests
SUMMARY: The Biden administration will spend $1 million on a study of how to train drug addicts how to distribute COVID-19 rapid tests to fellow drug addicts.

TITLE: Germany is 'fully decoupling' from Russia, eyes China as 'systemic' rival: German minister of state
SUMMARY: The minister of state spoke with Fox News Digital at the Aspen Security Forum, about the impact of winter on Europe's energy supply while the Russia-Ukraine war is still ongoing.

TITLE: Elon Musk confirms political candidates were subject to 'shadow-banning' by Twitter
SUMMARY: Twitter CEO Elon Musk has confirmed that the social media giant previously "shadow-banned" political candidates running for office.

TITLE: Democrats propose $1.75B abortion travel subsidy to get around ‘extreme’ state laws
SUMMARY: A new Democratic bill would offer $1.75B in federal subsidies to travel to different states to get abortions after the Supreme Court left abortion policy to the states.

TITLE: GOP senator to hold defense nominees over DOD’s ‘irresponsible’ abortion policy
SUMMARY: Senator Tuberville is threatening to block Defense Department nominees until DOD rescinds its new abortion policy, which Tuberville said is 'irresponsible.'

TITLE: Twitter Files: Unanswered questions remain after 'shadowban' revelations
SUMMARY: The Twitter Files Part 2 revealed that conservatives on the website were being censored but the extent of the suppression is still unknown, as is the ideological breakdown of those hit.

TITLE: House Republican bill would expand fast removals of illegal immigrants, as Title 42’s end nears
SUMMARY: A new House bill would significantly expand the use of expedited removal to deport illegal immigrants encountered at the border, just as the Title 42 authority is ending.

TITLE: Stacey Abrams' new book launch features children’s author who wants to 'abolish prisons'
SUMMARY: Former Georgia gubernatorial candidate is hosting a launch with her new book featuring a children's author who supports abolishing prisons and defunding police.

TITLE: Sinema left 'Arizonans behind' before leaving party, state Dems say
SUMMARY: The Arizona Democratic Party released a statement responding to Senator Krysten Sinema's decision to leave the Democratic Party to become an independent.

TITLE: Arizona Rep. Gallego accuses Sinema of prioritizing 'her own interests' after 'abandoning' Democratic Party
SUMMARY: Arizona Democrat Rep. Ruben Gallego is criticizing Sen. Kyrsten Sinema after she announced that she was leaving the Democratic Party on Friday.

TITLE: Senator-elect Fetterman cast in Christian Bale period film for his 'face that fits in the 1830s'
SUMMARY: John Fetterman, lieutenant governor and Senator-elect in Pennsylvania, will have a cameo in Netflix's new 1800s period film alongside well-known actor Christian Bale.

TITLE: Is Joe Manchin next? Strategists say the West Virginian isn’t about to leave the Democratic Party
SUMMARY: Will Manchin follow Kyrsten Sinema and abandon his party and toe a more independent line? Political strategists say that likelihood is as probable as the sun rising in the west.

TITLE: Biden administration sending $275 million in air defense, military aid to Ukraine
SUMMARY: The Biden administration will send Ukraine $275 million in military aid to support the country in its war with Russia.

TITLE: Schumer says Sinema flip won’t affect Dem control of the Senate, subpoena power intact
SUMMARY: Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer said Sen. Kyrsten Sinema's exit from the Democratic Party would have little impact on the chamber's business next Congress.

TITLE: 'Twitter Files': Republicans pledge 'accountability' for social media company's suppression of conservatives
SUMMARY: Several GOP lawmakers weighed in on the latest batch of "Twitter Files" released Thursday, with one saying it is "proof" Democrats and "embedded socialists" at the social media giant are interfering in U.S. elections.

TITLE: FBI investigating an unusual suspect: Israel
SUMMARY: The FBI is investigating the Israeli Defense Forces (IDF) after a Palestinian-American journalist was killed in the West Bank seven months ago, sparking controversy.

TITLE: Nonbinary Biden official Sam Brinton accused of grand larceny amid separate theft charges
SUMMARY: Sam Brinton, the nonbinary Energy Department official who leads nuclear waste policy, was charged with grand larceny of an item valued between $1,200 and $5,000 this week.

TITLE: Fox News crew witnesses dramatic human smuggling busts by Texas authorities
SUMMARY: Texas Department of Public Safety stopped a number of illegal immigrants seeking to escape into the U.S. interior this week, amid a historic number of gotaways.

TITLE: 2024 Watch: John Bolton says if he runs for president, ‘it'll be to win it’
SUMMARY: Former national security adviser John Bolton says that if he decides to run for the 2024 Republican presidential nomination, “I would get in to win it, not simply to make a point"

TITLE: University of Washington sued for withholding docs detailing professor's alleged role in DHS disinfo campaign
SUMMARY: A watchdog group sued the University of Washington for its failure to provide documents on how one of its professors allegedly coordinated with DHS on disinformation.

TITLE: AOC hits Sinema for leaving Democratic Party, registering as an independent: 'People deserve more'
SUMMARY: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, D-N.Y. criticized Sen. Kyrsten Sinema after the Arizona senator announced her decision to become independent.

TITLE: Elon Musk's 'Twitter Files' reveal internal debate to remove Mike Huckabee tweet including election joke
SUMMARY: Members of Twitter's former 2020 election enforcement slack channel considered removing an election related-joke from the platform during the election.

TITLE: Federal judge declines to hold former President Trump in contempt of court in classified material battle
SUMMARY: A federal judge on Friday declined to take action against former President Trump through contempt of court for allegedly failing to comply with a subpoena.

TITLE: Elon Musk says ‘election interference’ by social media companies ‘is wrong,’ undermines democracy
SUMMARY: Twitter CEO Elon Musk said social media companies should not interfere with political elections, especially to the benefit of one party or one party's candidate.

TITLE: GOP lawmakers respond to latest 'Twitter Files' detailing Trump's ban, vow Big Tech will 'be held accountable'
SUMMARY: Republican lawmakers, including Sen. Josh Hawley and Rep. Jim Jordan, responded to the latest installment of the "Twitter Files" which were released on Friday afternoon.

TITLE: Sinema's exit from Democratic Party opens the door for a GOP pickup — Could she run as a Republican?
SUMMARY: Arizona Sen. Kyrsten Sinema does not plan to caucus with Republicans and would not comment on her re-election ambitions, in an interview with CNN's Jake Tapper.

TITLE: Former GOP congressman says Republicans, Democrats could expand majorities by inviting independents
SUMMARY: Former Rep. David Jolly, who became an independent after leaving the House, said independent voters could help Republicans and Democrats expand their majorities.

TITLE: RNC, Arizona AG nominee file lawsuit contesting certified results, point to 'errors and inaccuracies'
SUMMARY: Arizona Republican attorney general nominee Abraham Hamadeh and the RNC have refiled their lawsuit alleging incompetence and voting irregularities impacted the election results.
